FT  25 NOV 94 / Observer: Shadowy
Wise move by Labour to unveil its shadow budget yesterday at Church House,
Westminster? It will be recalled that shadow chancellor Gordon Brown had
earlier defined the terms governing the validity of tax and spending
commitments made by Labour MPs. On BBC radio, Brown said: 'Unless you can
quote me chapter and verse about commitments made in the House of Commons,
then they were not made.'
